ereotypes of rural Americans as passive, ignorant, and uneducated, his interlocutors offer significant insight into the contemporary United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCountry lifezTexas. 0aEthnologyzTexas. 0aSexual minoritieszTexas. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023685?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023685423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023685/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles